  </p>

  <h2>1. What sellbonds.now is</h2>
  <p>
    sellbonds.now provides open-source software and public information for interacting with
    immutable smart contracts deployed on public blockchains (the “Protocol”). The Interface does
    not custody funds or keys, does not execute transactions on your behalf, does not match or
    broker trades, and runs no server in the transaction path. Transactions are signed locally by
    you (or by software you run) and submitted to a public network we do not control.
  </p>

  <h2>2. No offer, no advice, no endorsement</h2>
  <p>
    Nothing on the Interface is an offer to sell or a solicitation to buy any security or other
    financial instrument, or investment, legal, tax, or accounting advice. Bond listings are
    unverified, issuer-provided information read from public chain state. Display of a bond is not
    an endorsement of its issuer or its terms.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Eligibility and compliance are your responsibility</h2>
  <p>
    You may use the Interface only if doing so is lawful where you live and you are not subject to
    sanctions or listed on any sanctions list. Depending on your jurisdiction and how you use the
    Protocol, issuing, offering, or funding bonds may be regulated activity (including under
    securities, lending, AML, and tax law). <strong>You are solely responsible for determining
    whether your use is lawful and for complying with all applicable law.</strong> The Protocol
    itself performs no KYC and no sanctions screening — see the
    <a href="/risk">Risk Disclosure</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Risks</h2>
  <p>
    Using the Protocol involves substantial risk, including total loss of funds. The
    <a href="/risk">Risk Disclosure</a> is part of these terms. Read it.
  </p>

  <h2>5. As-is, no warranty</h2>
  <p>
    The Interface and the Protocol are provided <strong>“as is” and “as available”, without
    warranties of any kind</strong>, express or implied — including merchantability, fitness for a
    particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Interface or the Protocol
    is secure, error-free, or uninterrupted, or that the contracts are free of vulnerabilities.
    The contracts are an unaudited fork of Wildcat Protocol V2.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, sellbonds.now and its contributors shall not be liable
    for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or exemplary damages, or for any loss of
    funds, profits, data, or goodwill, arising from or related to your use of the Interface or the
