    limited to $100 in aggregate.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Non-custodial means non-recoverable</h2>
  <p>
    We cannot access, freeze, seize, reverse, or recover funds or keys. Anything you or your
    software does with the Protocol — including anything an AI agent does with a wallet you gave
    it — is your responsibility.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>
    Don't use the Interface to break the law — including money laundering, sanctions evasion,
    fraud, or market manipulation — and don't attack, overload, or attempt to disrupt the
    Interface (the testnet dispenser included).
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update the Interface and these terms at any time; the current version lives at this
    URL. Continued use after a change is acceptance. The Protocol's deployed contracts are
    immutable and unaffected by changes to these terms.
  </p>

